name: Lori Lorusso
bio:
Lori is the Open Source Program Manager at JFrog. She has a passion and enthusiasm for working with the developer community and has traveled across the globe attending conferences and community events advocating on behalf of developers.
 
 Lori was elected Marketing Chair of the CNCF, appointed Chair of the CDF Outreach Committee, is the program chair of cdCon, and is active in the OpenSSF outreach committee. She is a co-organizer of VJUG and frequently volunteers to support other JUGs at virtual and in person events. She co-hosts the CD Pipeline on behalf of the CDF with TechstrongTV. She is committed to helping open source and other tech communities grow and adapt in our ever changing environment.
